%2Fsupport.desk.com%2Fcustomer%2Fportal%2Farticles%2F566436&amp;sa=D&amp;sntz=1&amp;usg=AFQjCNEiJtMlDsCf157btfHFbtw1Q84EQw\">Adding Translated Content to your Knowledge Base</a></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"c7 c2\"><span class=\"c6\">Once the content is in the system, you can use it in Business Rules, Filters, and Macros to enable your agents to provide support in all the languages that you have enabled. Here&rsquo;s how: </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"c2 c7\"><span class=\"c10\"><a class=\"c9\" href=\"https://support.desk.com/customer/portal/articles/566490\">Responding to Cases with Translated Content</a></span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"c7 c2\"><a name=\"h.5ixqncxbhqcs\"></a><span>Managing your Multilingual Content</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"c7 c2\"><span class=\"c1\">Step 1: </span><span class=\"c6\">Track the status of your content with the </span><span class=\"c6\">Translation Management System. It alert you of outdated content with &quot;traffic-light&quot;-like graphics to the status of an article: </span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol class=\"c0\" start=\"1\">\r\n\t<li class=\"c3 c2\"><span class=\"c6\">Up-to-date (needing no revision), </span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"c3 c2\"><span class=\"c6\">In draft format (not displayed on your help center), </span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"c3 c2\"><span class=\"c6\">Outdated (out of synch with the current english revision of the article)</span></li>\r\n\t<li class=\"c2 c3\"><span class=\"c6\">Missing (no version of this content exists for the selected language)</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"c7 c2\"><img height=\"202\" src=\"http://desk-customers.s3.amazonaws.com/support/images/21.jpg\" width=\"549\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c1\">Step 2: </span><span class=\"c6\">To signal that a version of an article is not up to date, simply check </span><span class=\"c6\">&quot;Mark translated versions of this article outdated&quot; box when editing the article in Content Management: </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"c7 c2\"><img