ny questions relating to what Desk.com can do for you, general features and functions of the service, and troubleshoot of any and all Desk.com defects, there are some things our team is not able to do. This includes:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t\tWriting or reviewing custom code or markup.</li>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t\tLogging into or otherwise accessing systems, codebases, or sites outside of Desk.com.</li>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t\tAdding or manipulating data related to custom Desk.com sites, including:\r\n\t\t<ul>\r\n\t\t\t<li>\r\n\t\t\t\tAdvanced template editing.</li>\r\n\t\t\t<li>\r\n\t\t\t\tCreating or editing regular expressions.</li>\r\n\t\t\t<li>\r\n\t\t\t\tManipulating the output of liquid variables.</li>\r\n\t\t</ul>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDesk.com also provides a REST API that allows access to a variety of information related to your account. In the case of an integration with our API, our support team is available for &nbsp;general assistance and documentation, but is not prepared to assist with advanced troubleshooting. If you encounter API integration issues, we highly encourage that you approach the technical staff responsible for building the integration&mdash;they have a complete view of your configuration, products, and integrations, and should always be the first line of response when questions arise.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo get help with your Desk.com account, check out our <a href=\"http://support.desk.com\" target=\"_blank\">Support Center</a> for documentation, as well as the <a href=\"http://www.google.com/url?q=http%3A%2F%2Fsupport.desk.com%2Fcustomer%2Fportal%2Ftopics%2F2647-community-questions%2Fquestions&amp;sa=D&amp;sntz=1&amp;usg=AFQjCNF3mqq51y7Qx4BS4gNdVmq5Zl181A\" target=\"_blank\">Community Discussions</a> to see if other customers have similar questions. To learn more about our API, check out our <a href=\"http://www.google.com/url?q=http%3A%2F%2Fsupport.desk.com%2Fcustomer%2Fportal%2Ftopics%2F2647-community-questions%2Fquestions&amp;sa=D