/api/v2/articles/1021422","class":"article"},"topic":{"href":"/api/v2/topics/512525","class":"topic"},"translations":{"href":"/api/v2/articles/1021422/translations","class":"article_translation"}}},{"subject":"Customizing the Contact Us Form in your Support Center","body":"<p>Desk.com enables you to listen to customer inquiries from many channels. One of the most popular ways to get information from your customers is to use a <strong>contact form</strong> to standardize this information and bring it into your system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you&#39;re placing a contact form on another site that you run, you are probably using the <a href=\"http://support.desk.com/customer/portal/articles/1835-how-do-i-add-an-email-form-to-my-website-\">Desk.com Email Widget</a>.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you&#39;re customizing your Desk.com Support Center, you&#39;ll want to edit the email or &quot;Contact Us&quot; form to meet your needs. This form is shipped out of the box with Desk.com and gives you the ability to take input from your web visitors and conduct what we call a &quot;Pre-Create&quot; Search: presenting articles to users that might answer their question without having to complete a form and send you an issue - along with opening a case in your Desk.com site.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em><strong>Note:</strong> In order to customize your Contact Us form, you will need to use Advanced Templates, which is available with the Desk.com Plus Plan. To learn more about the different plans available, please visit our <a href=\"http://www.desk.com/pricing\">pricing page.</a>&nbsp;</em><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Getting Started</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>If you&#39;d like to customize your &quot;Contact Us&quot; form, visit <strong>Channels --&gt; Support Center --&gt; Web Templates</strong> and click <strong>Add Template</strong>&nbsp;to create a new template that Desk.com will use in your Support Center. Name the template with an easy-to-reference name, and begin customizing your email form.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>Editing the Initial Contact Form</h5>\r\n\r\n<p>To make changes to the initial contact form seen by web visitors, enter <strong>Advanced Mode</strong>&nbsp;in the template you just created. Make your changes on the <strong>Email (New) </strong> page to change the HTML presented to the web viewer when she opens a form - and you can test this at http://<em>yoursite</em>.Desk.com/customer/portal/emails/new.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Note:</strong> if you&#39;d like to skip the &quot;Pre-Create&quot; form, you can replace the following code:<br />\r\n&nbsp;{{form_begin}}<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWith:<br />\r\n&nbsp;{{form_begin|replace:&#39;/customer/portal/emails/pre_create&#39;,&#39;/customer/portal/emails&#39;}}</p>\r\nThis line sets the form action for your contact form to bypass the &quot;Pre-Create&quot; search.\r\n\r\n<h5>Editing the &quot;Pre-Create&quot; Form</h5>\r\nIn the same editor, the <strong>Email (Pre-Create)</strong>&nbsp;page manages the layout and display of the information presented to the visitor after a contact form is submitted. The default behavior of the form provides the top three results that are either articles or community questions related to your search. You can edit this page to change either the look and feel or the data displayed in the &quot;Pre-Create&quot; page. When they use this feature, our clients have seen significant increase in user self-service and have lowered the overall number of tickets created.<br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5>Editing the &quot;Completion&quot; Form</h5>\r\nThe <strong>Email (Submitted)</strong> page manages the layout and display of the contact form after it has been submitted. You may wish to provide additional information here, or simply thank the customer for sharing feedback.<br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5>Adding Validation or Changing the Validation in the Contact Form</h5>\r\nThis example demonstrates one way to customize the validation in the contact form:<br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div style=\"margin-left:20px;\"><a href=\"https://gist.github.com/8f9a160b0051bcdeae6a\">https://gist.github.com/8f9a160b0051bcdeae6a</a></div>\r\n<br />\r\nIt shows how to add two additional fields (in this case, the fields customer_first_name and customer_last_name, which use the special value of customer[first_name] and customer[last_name] to pass these values directly into the customer record.<br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5>Adding Custom Fields to the Contact Form</h5>\r\n\r\n<p>For more information on customizing this form to add custom fields, please read&nbsp;<a href=\"http://support.desk.com/customer/portal/articles/72841\">Using Custom Fields Throughout the Product</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Related Articles</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t<p><a href=\"http://support.desk.com/customer/portal/articles/1835-how-do-i-add-an-email-form-to-my-website-\">How do I add an Email Form to My Website?</a></p>\r\n\t</li>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t<p><a href=\"http://support.desk.com/customer/portal/articles/3085-how-do-i-add-a-chat-form-to-my-site-\">How do I add a Chat Form to my Site?</a></p>\r\n\t</li>\r\n\t<li>\r\n\t<p><a href=\"http://support.desk.com/customer/portal/articles/240552\">Understanding Pages in the Customer Help Center</a></p>\r\n\t</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n","body_email":"Desk.com enables you to listen to customer inquiries from many channels. One of the most popular ways to get information from your customers is to use a contact form to standardize this information and bring it into your system.\n\nIf you're placing a contact form on another site that you run, you are probably using the Desk.com Email Widget. \n\nIf you're customizing your Desk.com Support Center, you'll want to edit the email or \"Contact Us\" form to meet your needs. This form is shipped out of the box with Desk.com and gives you the ability to take input from your web visitors and conduct what we call a \"Pre-Create\" Search: presenting articles to users that might answer their question without having to complete a form and send you an issue - along with opening a case in your Desk.com site.\n\nNote: In order to customize your Contact Us form, you will need to use Advanced Templates, which is available with the Desk.com Plus Plan. To learn more about the different plans available, please visit our pricing page. \n \r\n\r\n Getting Started \r\n\r\n If you'd like to customize your \"Contact Us\" form, visit Channels --&gt; Support Center --&gt; Web Templates and click Add Template to create a new template that Desk.com will use in your Support Center. Name the template with an easy-to-reference name, and begin customizing your email form. \r\n\r\n Editing the Initial Contact Form \r\n\r\n To make changes to the initial contact form seen by web visitors, enter Advanced Mode in the template you just created. Make your changes on the Email (New)  page to change the HTML presented to the web viewer when she opens a form - and you can test this at http://yoursite.Desk.com/customer/portal/emails/new.\n\nNote: if you'd like to skip the \"Pre-Create\" form, you can replace the following code:\n{{form_begin}}\n\nWith:\n{{form_begin|replace:'/customer/portal/emails/pre_create','/customer/portal/emails'}} \r\nThis line sets the form action for your contact form to bypass the \"Pre-Create\" search.\r\n\r\n Editing the \"Pre-Create\" Form \r\nIn the same editor, the Email (Pre-Create) page manages the layout and display of the information presented to the visitor after a contact form is submitted. The default behavior of the form provides the top three results that are either articles or community questions related to your search. You can edit this page to change either the look and feel or the data displayed in the \"Pre-Create\" page. When they use this feature, our clients have seen significant increase in user self-service and have lowered the overall number of tickets created.\n Editing the \"Completion\" Form \r\nThe Email (Submitted) page manages the layout and display of the contact form after it has been submitted. You may wish to provide additional information here, or simply thank the customer for sharing feedback.\n Adding Validation or Changing the Validation in the Contact Form \r\nThis example demonstrates one way to customize the validation in the contact form:\n https://gist.github.com/8f9a160b0051bcdeae6a \r\n\nIt shows how to add two additional fields (in this case, the fields customer_first_name and customer_last_name, which use the special value of customer[first_name] and customer[last_name] to pass these values directly into the customer record.\n Adding Custom Fields to the Contact Form \r\n\r\n For more information on customizing this form to add custom fields, please read Using Custom Fields Throughout the Product. \r\n\r\n Related Articles \r\n\r\n  \r\n How do I add an Email Form to My Website? \r\n \r\n \r\n How do I add a Chat Form to my Site? \r\n \r\n \r\n Understanding Pages in the Customer Help Center","body_email_auto":true,"body_chat":"Desk.com enables you to listen to customer inquiries from many channels. One of the most popular ways to get information from your customers is to use a contact form to standardize this information and bring it into your system.If you're placing a co... http://j.mp/tMMv3L","body_chat_auto":true,"body_web_callback":"<p>Desk.com enables you to listen to customer inquiries from many channels. One of the most popular ways to get information from your customers is to use a <strong>contact form</strong> to standardize this information and bring it into your system.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you&#39;re placing a contact form on another site that you run, you are probably using the <a href=\"http://support.desk.com/customer/portal/articles/1835-how-do-i-add-an-email-form-to-my-website-\">Desk.com Email Widget</a>.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you&#39;re customizing your Desk.com Support Center, you&#39;ll want to edit the email or &quot;Contact Us&quot; form to meet your needs. This form is shipped out of the box with De