 \r\n\r\n \nLiquid/HTML Code Snippet \r\n\r\n This code does the following: \r\n\r\n  in a div, writes out a header and then prepares a table to hold the contents of a topic loop \r\n using a for loop, checks to see if the article count of the topic is greater than 0, and if so, writes out HTML \r\n uses the Cycle Liquid tag to create a two column layout within the table \r\n in an additional table, does a similar loop and checks to see if the question count of the topic is greater than 0, and if so, writes out HTML \r\n uses the Cycle Liquid tag to create another two column layout \r\n    \r\n \r\n\r\n  &lt;div class='content dashboard'&gt; \r\n\r\n       &lt;h3&gt;Browse By Topic&lt;/h3&gt; \r\n\r\n    &lt;!-- start center content topic listing --&gt;   \r\n\r\n     {% if topics_count &gt; 0 %} \r\n\r\n    &lt;!-- write topics for article topics --&gt; \r\n\r\n       &lt;table width='100%' cellspacing='0'&gt; \r\n\r\n        {% for topic in topics offset:1 %} \r\n\r\n         {% if topic.article_count &gt; 0 %} \r\n\r\n {% cycle 'begin': '&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;', '&lt;td&gt;' %}  \r\n\r\n &lt;div class='topic topic{{ topic.id }}'&gt; \r\n\r\n  &lt;h4&gt;{{ topic.name }}&lt;/h4&gt;           \r\n\r\n &lt;h5 class='articles'&gt; \r\n\r\n  {{ topic.article_count }} \r\n\r\n  {{ 'Article' | pluralize: topic.article_count }} \r\n\r\n  &lt;a href='{{ topic.public_articles_url }}'&gt;View All&lt;/a&gt; \r\n\r\n &lt;/h5&gt; \r\n\r\n &lt;ul&gt; \r\n\r\n {% for article in topic.articles limit:5 %} \r\n\r\n &lt;li&gt; \r\n\r\n &lt;a href='{{ article.public_url }}'&gt;{{ article.subject_plain | clip:40 }}&lt;/a&gt; \r\n\r\n &lt;/li&gt; \r\n\r\n {% endfor %} \r\n\r\n &lt;/ul&gt; \r\n\r\n &lt;/div&gt; \r\n\r\n {% cycle 'endcolumn': '&lt;/td&gt;', '&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;' %}  \r\n\r\n {% endif %} \r\n\r\n {% endfor %} \r\n\r\n       &lt;/table&gt; \r\n\r\n     &lt;!--- end table for article topics --&gt; \r\n\r\n   \r\n\r\n     &lt;!--- start table for question topics --&gt; \r\n\r\n    {% if site.questions_enabled_config %} \r\n\r\n     &lt;table width='100%' cellspacing='0'&gt; \r\n\r\n        {% for topic in topics offset:1 %} \r\n\r\n         {% if topic.question_count &gt; 0 %} \r\n\r\n         {% cycle 'begin': '&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;', '&lt;td&gt;' %}  \r\n\r\n         &lt;div class='topic topic{{ topic.id }}'&gt; \r\n\r\n               &lt;h4&gt;{{ topic.name }}&lt;/h4&gt; \r\n\r\n                   &lt;h5 class='questions'&gt; \r\n\r\n                     Recent Q&amp;amp;A \r\n\r\n                     &lt;a href='{{ topic.public_questions_url }}'&gt;View All&lt;/a&gt; \r\n\r\n                   &lt;/h5&gt; \r\n\r\n                   &lt;ul&gt; \r\n\r\n                     {% for question in topic.questions limit:5 %} \r\n\r\n                       {% if question.featured? %} \r\n\r\n                         &lt;li class='featured'&gt; \r\n\r\n                           &lt;a href='{{ question.public_url }}'&gt;{{ question.subject_plain | clip:40 }}&lt;/a&gt; \r\n\r\n                         &lt;/li&gt; \r\n\r\n                       {% else %} \r\n\r\n                         &lt;li&gt; \r\n\r\n                           &lt;a href='{{ question.public_url }}'&gt;{{ question.subject_plain | clip:40 }}&lt;/a&gt; \r\n\r\n                         &lt;/li&gt; \r\n\r\n                       {% endif %} \r\n\r\n {% endfor %} \r\n\r\n &lt;/ul&gt; \r\n\r\n             &lt;/div&gt; \r\n\r\n         {% cycle 'endcolumn': '&lt;/td&gt;', '&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;' %}  \r\n\r\n           {% endif %} \r\n\r\n         {% endfor %} \r\n\r\n       &lt;/table&gt; \r\n\r\n   \r\n\r\n {%endif%} \r\n\r\n   \r\n\r\n     &lt;!--- end table for question topics --&gt; \r\n\r\n   \r\n\r\n       {% else %} \r\n\r\n         &lt;h4&gt;No topics are available.&lt;/h4&gt; \r\n\r\n       {% endif %} \r\n\r\n   &lt;!--end center content topic listing--&gt; \r\n\r\n   \r\n\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;","body_phone_auto":true,"body_facebook":"Your Desk.com Help Center contains topics that can be used to display Articles, Questions, or Articles and Questions.\n\nWhen customizing your Help Center, you may want to separate visually topics that contain Articles from topics that contain Questions.\n\nThis article demonstrates one layout for your Help Center Index page that accomplishes that design goal. \r\n\r\n \nSteps to Build \r\n\r\n  login to your Desk.com Admin site \r\n Visit the Channels &gt; Help Center Section \r\n Make a new Template and title it \"Separate Articles from QNA\" \r\n Enter the Advanced Template Editor \r\n Replace or comment out the existing div having the class \"content dashboard\" and containing a loop of Topics \r\n Save and test this code to confirm that it does what you'd like \r\n    \r\n\r\n \nWhat you'll Need \r\n\r\n  A Desk.com user having rights to edit Templates and/or Add Features (Administrator or Billing Adminstrator) \r\n Some knowledge of HTML and Liquid to customize your page \r\n A Desk.com site with the Help Center and Question Channel enabled \r\n At least two Knowledge Base topics (one with at least one article, and one with at least one question) \r\n    \r\n\r\n \nLiquid/HTML Code Snippet \r\n\r\n This code does the following: \r\n\r\n  in a div, writes out a header and then prepares a table to hold the contents of a topic loop \r\n using a for loop, checks to see if the article count of the topic is greater than 0, and if so, writes out HTML \r\n uses the Cycle Liquid tag to create a two column layout within the table \r\n in an additional table, does a similar loop and checks to see if the question count of the topic is greater than 0, and if so, writes out HTML \r\n uses the Cycle Liquid tag to create another two column layout \r\n    \r\n \r\n\r\n  &lt;div class='content dashboard'&gt; \r\n\r\n       &lt;h3&gt;Browse By Topic&lt;/h3&gt; \r\n\r\n    &lt;!-- start center content topic listing --&gt;   \r\n\r\n     {% if topics_count &gt; 0 %} \r\n\r\n    &lt;!-- write topics for article topics --&gt; \r\n\r\n       &lt;table width='100%' cellspacing='0'&gt; \r\n\r\n        {% for topic in topics offset:1 %} \r\n\r\n         {% if topic.article_count &gt; 0 %} \r\n\r\n {% cycle 'begin': '&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;', '&lt;td&gt;' %}  \r\n\r\n &lt;div class='topic topic{{ topic.id }}'&gt; \r\n\r\n  &lt;h4&gt;{{ topic.name }}&lt;/h4&gt;           \r\n\r\n &lt;h5 class='articles'&gt; \r\n\r\n  {{ topic.article_count }} \r\n\r\n  {{ 'Article' | pluralize: topic.article_count }} \r\n\r\n  &lt;a href='{{ topic.public_articles_url }}'&gt;View All&lt;/a&gt; \r\n\r\n &lt;/h5&gt; \r\n\r\n &lt;ul&gt; \r\n\r\n {% for article in topic.articles limit:5 %} \r\n\r\n &lt;li&gt; \r\n\r\n &lt;a href='{{ article.public_url }}'&gt;{{ article.subject_plain | clip:40 }}&lt;/a&gt; \r\n\r\n &lt;/li&gt; \r\n\r\n {% endfor %} \r\n\r\n &lt;/ul&gt; \r\n\r\n &lt;/div&gt; \r\n\r\n {% cycle 'endcolumn': '&lt;/td&gt;', '&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;' %}  \r\n\r\n {% endif %} \r\n\r\n {% endfor %} \r\n\r\n       &lt;/table&gt; \r\n\r\n     &lt;!--- end table for article topics --&gt; \r\n\r\n   \r\n\r\n     &lt;!--- start table for question topics --&gt; \r\n\r\n    {% if site.questions_enabled_config %} \r\n\r\n     &lt;table width='100%' cellspacing='0'&gt; \r\n\r\n        {% for topic in topics offset:1 %} \r\n\r\n         {% if topic.question_count &gt; 0 %} \r\n\r\n         {% cycle 'begin': '&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;', '&lt;td&gt;' %}  \r\n\r\n         &lt;div class='topic topic{{ topic.id }}'&gt; \r\n\r\n               &lt;h4&gt;{{ topic.name }}&lt;/h4&gt; \r\n\r\n                   &lt;h5 class='questions'&gt; \r\n\r\n                     Recent Q&amp;amp;A \r\n\r\n                     &lt;a href='{{ topic.public_questions_url }}'&gt;View All&lt;/a&gt; \r\n\r\n                   &lt;/h5&gt; \r\n\r\n                   &lt;ul&gt; \r\n\r\n                     {% for question in topic.questions limit:5 %} \r\n\r\n                       {% if question.featured? %} \r\n\r\n                         &lt;li class='featured'&gt; \r\n\r\n                           &lt;a href='{{ question.public_url }}'&gt;{{ question.subject_plain | clip:40 }}&lt;/a&gt; \r\n\r\n                         &lt;/li&gt; \r\n\r\n                       {% else %} \r\n\r\n                         &lt;li&gt; \r\n\r\n                           &lt;a href='{{ question.public_url }}'&gt;{{ question.subject_plain | clip:40 }}&lt;/a&gt; \r\n\r\n                         &lt;/li&gt; \r\n\r\n                       {% endif %} \r\n\r\n {% endfor %} \r\n\r\n &lt;/ul&gt; \r\n\r\n             &lt;/div&gt; \r\n\r\n         {% cycle 'endcolumn': '&lt;/td&gt;', '&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;' %}  \r\n\r\n           {% endif %} \r\n\r\n         {% endfor %} \r\n\r\n       &lt;/table&gt; \r\n\r\n   \r\n\r\n {%endif%} \r\n\r\n   \r\n\r\n     &lt;!--- end table for question topics --&gt; \r\n\r\n   \r\n\r\n       {% else %} \r\n\r\n         &lt;h4&gt;No topics are available.&lt;/h4&gt; \r\n\r\n       {% endif %} \r\n\r\n   &lt;!--end center content topic listing--&gt; \r\n\r\n   \r\n\r\n     &lt;/div&gt;","body_facebook_auto":true,"keywords":"article, question, topics, topic, ","position":15,"quickcode":null,"in_support_center":true,"internal_notes":"","publish_at":"2013-05-10T00:00:00Z","created_at":"2012-02-16T23:40:39Z","updated_at":"2013-05-13T17:57:13Z","_links":{"self":{"href":"/api/v2/articles/376026","class":"article"},"topic":{"href":"/api/v2/topics/512525","class":"topic"},"translations":{"href":"/api/v2/articles/376026/translations","class":"article_translation"}}},{"subject":"Configuring your Support Center for Read-Only Access During Maintenance","body":"During desk maintenance windows, the Customer Help Center will be in read-only mode. This means users will not be able to submit email requests, update QNAs, initiate chat, or rate articles.&nbsp; We&#39;ve added a liquid attribute called &quot;{{read_only}}&quot; that you can use to create a modified version of your Help Center during Maintenance outages. This attribute returns True when the read-only feature is in effect.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCustomers who use the Advanced Help Center Templates should make the following changes to their sites to give customers the best experience possible when the Read-only feature is enabled:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Change the email link from the form to an emailto: to the default inbound mailbox address<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Remove the &quot;Rate Article&quot; links from KB Articles<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hide the chat link (if using chat)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Hide the link to submit a new qna case (if using QNA)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Replace the &quot;post an response&quot; section to qna with a message that QNA responses are currently not available (if using QNA)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFor all of these steps, you will need to edit your Help Center Templates. Do this by taking the following steps:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n1) Find your Support Center web template at yoursite.desk.com /admin/channels/support-center/web-templates;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2) Enter Advanced Mode for your template.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNow, find the changes you need to make below.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nChange the Email Link from the Form to the Mailto:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUse the following steps to change the email link from the email form to a &quot;mailto: link&quot; during Read-only operation:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n1) go to the Layout section;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2) find the text that reads:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n{% if site.email_enabled_config %}<br />\r\n&lt;li&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;a href=&#39;{{email_link}}&#39;&gt;Email Us&lt;/a&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;/li&gt;<br />\r\n{% endif %}<br />\r\n<br />\r\nand change this text to:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n{% if site.email_enabled_config %}<br />\r\n&lt;li&gt;<br />\r\n{% unless read_only %}<br />\r\n&lt;a href=&#39;{{email_link}}&#39;&gt;Email Us&lt;/a&gt;<br />\r\n{%else%}<br />\r\n&lt;a href=&#39;mailto:example@youremail.com}}&#39;&gt;Email Us&lt;/a&gt;<br />\r\n{% endunless %}<br />\r\n&lt;/li&gt;<br />\r\n{% endif %}<br />\r\n<br />\r\nRemove the Rate Article links from KB Articles:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUse the following steps to remove the Rate Article links from KB articles during Read-only operation:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n1) go to the Page (Article) section;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2) find the text that reads:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n{% if rate_article == true %}<br />\r\n{{ rate_block }}<br />\r\n{% endif %}<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\nand wrap it with an Unless block, e.g.:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n{% unless read_only %}<br />\r\n{% if rate_article == true %}<br />\r\n{{ rate_block }}<br />\r\n{% endif %}<br />\r\n{% endunless %}<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHide the Chat Link (if necessary):<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUse the following steps to hide the Chat link during Read-only operation:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n1) go to the Layout section;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2) find the text that reads:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n{% if site.chat_enabled_config %}<br />\r\n&lt;li&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;a href=&#39;{{chat_link}}&#39;&gt;Live Chat!&lt;/a&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;/li&gt;<br />\r\n{% endif %}<br />\r\n<br />\r\nand change this text to:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n{% if site.chat_enabled_config %}<br />\r\n{% unless read_only %}<br />\r\n&lt;li&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;a href=&#39;{{chat_link}}&#39;&gt;Live Chat!&lt;/a&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;/li&gt;<br />\r\n{% endunless %}<br />\r\n{% endif %}<br />\r\n<br />\r\nHide the QNA Link (if necessary):<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUse the following steps to hide the link to submit a new question during Read-only operation:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n1) go to the Layout section;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2) find the text that reads:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n{% if site.questions_enabled_config %}<br />\r\n&lt;li&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;a href=&#39;{{qna_link}}&#39;&gt;Post a Question&lt;/a&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;/li&gt;<br />\r\n{% endif %}<br />\r\n<br />\r\nand change this text to:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n{% if site.questions_enabled_config %}<br />\r\n{% unless read_only %}<br />\r\n&lt;li&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;a href=&#39;{{qna_link}}&#39;&gt;Post a Question&lt;/a&gt;<br />\r\n&lt;/li&gt;<br />\r\n{% endunless %}<br />\r\n{% endif %}<br />\r\n<br />\r\nReplace the Post a Response Link (if necessary):<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUse the following steps to hide the link to post a QNA response during Read-only operation:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n1) go to the Q&amp;A (Show) section;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n2) find the text that reads:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n{% if question.allow_answers? != true or question.case.closed? %}<br />\r\n&lt;p class=&#39;form-notice&#39;&gt;This question is closed to new answers.&lt;/p&gt;<br />\r\n{% else %}<br />\r\n<br />\r\nand change this text to:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n{% if question.allow_answers? != true or question.case.closed? %}<br />\r\n&lt;p class=&#39;form-notice&#39;&gt;This question is closed to new answers.&lt;/p&gt;<br />\r\n{%elsif read_only%}<br />\r\n&lt;p class=&#39;form-notice&#39;&gt;The site is currently in read-only mode - you&#39;ll be able to submit a question when we come back&hellip;&lt;/p&gt;<br />\r\n{% else %}","body_email":"During desk maintenance windows, the Customer Help Center will be in read-only mode. This means users will not be able to submit email requests, update QNAs, initiate chat, or rate articles.  We've added a liquid attribute called \"{{read_only}}\" that you can use to create a modified version of your Help Center during Maintenance outages. This attribute returns True when the read-only feature is in effect.\n\nCustomers who use the Advanced Help Center Templates should make the following changes to their sites to give customers the best experience possible when the Read-only feature is enabled:\n\nChange the email link from the form to an emailto: to the default inbound mailbox address\nRemove the \"Rate Article\" links from KB Articles\nHide the chat link (if using chat)\nHide the link to submit a new qna case (if using QNA)\nReplace the \"post an response\" section to qna with a message that QNA responses are currently not available (if using QNA)\n\nFor all of these steps, you will need to edit your Help Center Templates. Do this by taking the following steps:\n\n1) Find your Support Center web template at yoursite.desk.com /admin/channels/support-center/web-templates;\n\n2) Enter Advanced Mode for your template.\n\nNow, find the changes you need to make below.\n\nChange the Email Link from the Form to the Mailto:\n\nUse the following steps to change the email link from the email form to a \"mailto: link\" during Read-only operation:\n\n1) go to the Layout section;\n\n2) find the text that reads:\n\n{% if site.email_enabled_config %}\n&lt;li&gt;\n&lt;a href='{{email_link}}'&gt;Email Us&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;/li&gt;\n{% endif %}\n\nand change this text to:\n\n{% if site.email_enabled_config %}\n&lt;li&gt;\n{% unless read_only %}\n&lt;a href='{{email_link}}'&gt;Email Us&lt;/a&gt;\n{%else%}\n&lt;a href='mailto:example@youremail.com}}'&gt;Email Us&lt;/a&gt;\n{% endunless %}\n&lt;/li&gt;\n{% endif %}\n\nRemove the Rate Article links from KB Articles:\n\nUse the following steps to remove the Rate Article links from KB articles during Read-only operation:\n\n1) go to the Page (Article) section;\n\n2) find the text that reads:\n\n{% if rate_article == true %}\n{{ rate_block }}\n{% endif %}\n\nand wrap it with an Unless block, e.g.:\n\n{% unless read_only %}\n{% if rate_article == true %}\n{{ rate_block }}\n{% endif %}\n{% endunless %}\n\nHide the Chat Link (if necessary):\n\nUse the following steps to hide the Chat link during Read-only operation:\n\n1) go to the Layout section;\n\n2) find the text that reads:\n\n{% if site.chat_enabled_config %}\n&lt;li&gt;\n&lt;a href='{{chat_link}}'&gt;Live Chat!&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;/li&gt;\n{% endif %}\n\nand change this text to:\n\n{% if site.chat_enabled_config %}\n{% unless read_only %}\n&lt;li&gt;\n&lt;a href='{{chat_link}}'&gt;Live Chat!&lt;/a&gt;\n&lt;/li&gt;\n{% endunless %}\n{% endif %}\n\nHide the QNA Link (if necessary):\n\