":true,"internal_notes":"","publish_at":"2013-05-10T00:00:00Z","created_at":"2011-12-13T00:37:20Z","updated_at":"2013-05-13T17:57:09Z","_links":{"self":{"href":"/api/v2/articles/273220","class":"article"},"topic":{"href":"/api/v2/topics/512525","class":"topic"},"translations":{"href":"/api/v2/articles/273220/translations","class":"article_translation"}}},{"subject":"How does Whole Company Support (AKA Flex Hours) work?","body":"When we developed pricing for each Desk.com plan, we talked to many of our early partners and a frequent request was the ability to have more people in an organization participate in the support process in one way or another. The need for participation in customer support spans developers, executives and others - not just dedicated support agents. We believe that everyone in your organization has a role in providing awesome support, and each person having understanding your customers&#39; needs is critical to your success. &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPricing models for most help desks made it prohibitive to put this into practice because they require a seat license for every user of the platform, including casual participants. After a lot of consideration, we came up with what we believe is a unique, genuine solution. Traditional seat licensing still makes sense for &quot;full-time&quot; support agents, but in order to bring the voice of the customer to the entire organization, we have created a supplemental option called &quot;Flex&quot; hours. The spirit of Flex hours is to allow users who are not &quot;full-time&quot; agents to participate in the support experience.\r\n<h4><strong>How Flex Hours Work</strong></h4>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;For your full-time support staff, buy traditional per-month seats<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;You can then create as many Flex agent accounts as you like (create seats for your executives, developers, etc. for FREE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;When Flex agents log into Desk.com, we track the total logged-in time<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;At the end of the month we total your Flex hours across all of your Flex agents<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Flex hours are charged @ $1 per hour\r\n<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<strong>Using Flex Hours</strong>\r\n\r\n<h4>So lets think about this in the context of a real example.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLets say your company has 25 employees. 5 of them are dedicated support people, but there are many others that you want to&nbsp;participate&nbsp;in the support process in some capacity. With Desk.com you would buy 5 &quot;full-time&quot; agent seats and create 20 &quot;Flex&quot; seats. If the CEO logs in for 5.5 hours during the month and a developer logs in for 10 minutes to help out, your total monthly cost would be 5 x $49 per &quot;full-time&quot; agent per month + 6 x $1 per &quot;Flex&quot; hour &nbsp;= $251 for the month.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNow everyone in your company is part of the process. &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe think this is very powerful&nbsp;and enables your entire company to rally around your customers.</h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Flex Bundles</strong><br />\r\nIf your business is able to foresee busy seasons or plans on hiring a part-time agent in the future, you have the ability to purchase a package of Flex Hours at a discounted price of up to 50% depending on how many hours you buy.&nbsp;<br />\r\nWith the Desk.com Plus Plan, you can purchase the following Flex Bundles:&nbsp;</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">&bull;20 hours = $18</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">&bull;50 hours = $40</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">&bull;100 hours = $70</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">&bull;250 hours = $150</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">&bull;500 hours = $250</h4>\r\n","body_email":"When we developed pricing for each Desk.com plan, we talked to many of our early partners and a frequent request was the ability to have more people in an organization participate in the support process in one way or another. The need for participation in customer support spans developers, executives and others - not just dedicated support agents. We believe that everyone in your organization has a role in providing awesome support, and each person having understanding your customers' needs is critical to your success.  \n\nPricing models for most help desks made it prohibitive to put this into practice because they require a seat license for every user of the platform, including casual participants. After a lot of consideration, we came up with what we believe is a unique, genuine solution. Traditional seat licensing still makes sense for \"full-time\" support agents, but in order to bring the voice of the customer to the entire organization, we have created a supplemental option called \"Flex\" hours. The spirit of Flex hours is to allow users who are not \"full-time\" agents to participate in the support experience.\r\n How Flex Hours Work \r\n    •    For your full-time support staff, buy traditional per-month seats\n•    You can then create as many Flex agent accounts as you like (create seats for your executives, developers, etc. for FREE)\n•    When Flex agents log into Desk.com, we track the total logged-in time\n•    At the end of the month we total your Flex hours across all of your Flex agents\n•    Flex hours are charged @ $1 per hour\r\n   \r\n\r\n   \r\nUsing Flex Hours\r\n\r\n So lets think about this in the context of a real example. \n\nLets say your company has 25 employees. 5 of them are dedicated support people, but there are many others that you want to participate in the support process in some capacity. With Desk.com you would buy 5 \"full-time\" agent seats and create 20 \"Flex\" seats. If the CEO logs in for 5.5 hours during the month and a developer logs in for 10 minutes to help out, your total monthly cost would be 5 x $49 per \"full-time\" agent per month + 6 x $1 per \"Flex\" hour  = $251 for the month.\n\nNow everyone in your company is part of the process.  \n\nWe think this is very powerful and enables your entire company to rally around your customers. \r\n \r\n\r\n Flex Bundles\nIf your business is able to foresee busy seasons or plans on hiring a part-time agent in the future, you have the ability to purchase a package of Flex Hours at a discounted price of up to 50% depending on how many hours you buy. \nWith the Desk.com Plus Plan, you can purchase the following Flex Bundles:  \r\n\r\n •20 hours = $18 \r\n\r\n •50 hours = $40 \r\n\r\n •100 hours = $70 \r\n\r\n •250 hours = $150 \r\n\r\n •500 hours = $250","body_email_auto":true,"body_chat":"When we developed pricing for each Desk.com plan, we talked to many of our early partners and a frequent request was the ability to have more people in an organization participate in the support process in one way or another. The need for participati... http://j.mp/hQr8Vt","body_chat_auto":true,"body_web_callback":"When we developed pricing for each Desk.com plan, we talked to many of our early partners and a frequent request was the ability to have more people in an organization participate in the support process in one way or another. The need for participation in customer support spans developers, executives and others - not just dedicated support agents. We believe that everyone in your organization has a role in providing awesome support, and each person having understanding your customers&#39; needs is critical to your success. &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPricing models for most help desks made it prohibitive to put this into practice because they require a seat license for every user of the platform, including casual participants. After a lot of consideration, we came up with what we believe is a unique, genuine solution. Traditional seat licensing still makes sense for &quot;full-time&quot; support agents, but in order to bring the voice of the customer to the entire organization, we have created a supplemental option called &quot;Flex&quot; hours. The spirit of Flex hours is to allow users who are not &quot;full-time&quot; agents to participate in the support experience.\r\n<h4><strong>How Flex Hours Work</strong></h4>\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;For your full-time support staff, buy traditional per-month seats<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;You can then create as many Flex agent accounts as you like (create seats for your executives, developers, etc. for FREE)<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;When Flex agents log into Desk.com, we track the total logged-in time<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;At the end of the month we total your Flex hours across all of your Flex agents<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Flex hours are charged @ $1 per hour\r\n<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<strong>Using Flex Hours</strong>\r\n\r\n<h4>So lets think about this in the context of a real example.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLets say your company has 25 employees. 5 of them are dedicated support people, but there are many others that you want to&nbsp;participate&nbsp;in the support process in some capacity. With Desk.com you would buy 5 &quot;full-time&quot; agent seats and create 20 &quot;Flex&quot; seats. If the CEO logs in for 5.5 hours during the month and a developer logs in for 10 minutes to help out, your total monthly cost would be 5 x $49 per &quot;full-time&quot; agent per month + 6 x $1 per &quot;Flex&quot; hour &nbsp;= $251 for the month.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNow everyone in your company is part of the process. &nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe think this is very powerful&nbsp;and enables your entire company to rally around your customers.</h4>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Flex Bundles</strong><br />\r\nIf your business is able to foresee busy seasons or plans on hiring a part-time agent in the future, you have the ability to purchase a package of Flex Hours at a discounted price of up to 50% depending on how many hours you buy.&nbsp;<br />\r\nWith the Desk.com Plus Plan, you can purchase the following Flex Bundles:&nbsp;</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">&bull;20 hours = $18</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">&bull;50 hours = $40</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">&bull;100 hours = $70</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">&bull;250 hours = $150</h4>\r\n\r\n<h4 style=\"text-align: center;\">&bull;500 hours = $250</h4>\r\n","body_web_callback_auto":true,"body_twitter":"When we developed pricing for each Desk.com plan, we talked to many of our early partners and a freque... https://support.desk.com/customer/portal/articles/3341-how-does-whole-company-support-aka-flex-hours-work-","body_twitter_auto":true,"body_qna":"When we developed pricing for each Desk.com plan, we talked to many of our early partners and a frequent request was the ability to have more people in an organization participate in the support process in one way or another. The need for participation in customer support spans developers, executives and others - not just dedicated support agents. We believe that everyone in your organization has a role in providing awesome support, and each person having understanding your customers' needs is critical to your success.  \n\nPricing models for most help desks made it prohibitive to put this into practice because they require a seat license for every user of the platform, including casual participants. After a lot of consideration, we came up with what we believe is a unique, genuine solution. Traditional seat licensing still makes sense for \"full-time\" support agents, but in order to bring the voice of the customer to the entire organization, we have created a supplemental option called \"Flex\" hours. The spirit of Flex hours is to allow users who are not \"full-time\" agents to participate in the support experience.\r\n How Flex Hours Work \r\n    •    For your full-time support staff, buy traditional per-month seats\n•    You can then create as many Flex agent accounts as you like (create seats for your executives, developers, etc. for FREE)\n•    When Flex agents log into Desk.com, we track the total logged-in time\n•    At the end of the month we total your Flex hours across all of your Flex agents\n•    Flex hours are charged @ $1 per hour\r\n   \r\n\r\n   \r\nUsing Flex Hours\r\n\r\n So lets think about this in the context of a real example. \n\nLets say your company has 25 employees. 5 of them are dedicated support people, but there are many others that you want to participate in the support process in some capacity. With Desk.com you would buy 5 \"full-time\" agent seats and create 20 \"Flex\" seats. If the CEO logs in for 5.5 hours during the month and a developer logs in for 10 minutes to help out, your total monthly cost would be 5 x $49 per \"full-time\" agent per month + 6 x $1 per \"Flex\" hour  = $251 for the month.\n\nNow everyone in your company is part of the process.  \n\nWe think this is very powerful and enables your entire company to rally around your customers. \r\n \r\n\r\n Flex Bundles\nIf your business is able to foresee busy seasons or plans on hiring a part-time agent in the future, you have the ability to purchase a package of Flex Hours at a discounted price of up to 50% depending on how many hours you buy. \nWith the Desk.com Plus Plan, you can purchase the following Flex Bundles:  \r\n\r\n •20 hours = $18 \r\n\r\n •50 hours = $40 \r\n\r\n •100 hours = $70 \r\n\r\n •250 hours = $150 \r\n\r\n •500 hours = $250","body_qna_auto":true,"body_phone":"When we developed pricing for each Desk.com plan, we talked to many of our early partners and a frequent request was the ability to have more people in an organization participate in the support process in one way or another. The need for participation in customer support spans developers, executives and others - not just dedicated support agents. We believe that everyone in your organization has a role in providing awesome support, and each person having understanding your customers' needs is critical to your success.  \n\nPricing models for most help desks made it prohibitive to put this into practice because they require a seat license for every user of the platform, including casual participants. After a lot of consideration, we came up with what we believe is a unique, genuine solution. Traditional seat licensing still makes sense for \"full-time\" support agents, but in order to bring the voice of the customer to the entire organization, we have created a supplemental option called \"Flex\" hours. The spirit of Flex hours is to allow users who are not \"full-time\" agents to participate in the support experience.\r\n How Flex Hours Work \r\n    •    For your full-time support staff, buy traditional per-month seats\n•    You can then create as many Flex agent accounts as you like (create seats for your executives, developers, etc. for FREE)\n•    When Flex agents log into Desk.com, we track the total logged-in time\n•    At the end of the month we total your Flex hours across all of your Flex agents\n•    Flex hours are charged @ $1 per hour\r\n   \r\n\r\n   \r\nUsing Flex Hours\r\n\r\n So lets think about this in the context of a real example. \n\nLets say your company has 25 employees. 5 of them are dedicated support people, but there are many others that you want to participate in the support process in some capacity. With Desk.com you would buy 5 \"full-time\" agent seats and create 20 \"Flex\" seats. If the CEO logs in for 5.5 hours during the month and a developer logs in for 10 minutes to help out, your total monthly cost would be 5 x $49 per \"full-time\" agent per month + 6 x $1 per \"Flex\" hour  = $251 for the month.\n\nNow everyone in your company is part of the process.  \n\nWe think this is very powerful and enables your entire company to rally around your customers. \r\n \r\n\r\n Flex Bundles\nIf your business is able to foresee busy seasons or plans on hiring a part-time agent in the future, you have the ability to purchase a package of Flex Hours at a discounted price of up to 50% depending on how many hours you buy. \nWith the Desk.com Plus Plan, you can purchase the following Flex Bundles:  \r\n\r\n •20 hours = $18 \r\n\r\n •50 hours = $40 \r\n\r\n •100 hours = $70 \r\n\r\n •250 hours = $150 \r\n\r\n •500 hours = $250","body_phone_auto":true,"body_facebook":"When we developed pricing for each Desk.com plan, we talked to many of our early partners and a frequent request was the ability to have more people in an organization participate in the support process in one way or another. The need for participation in customer support spans developers, executives and others - not just dedicated support agents. We believe that everyone in your organization has a role in providing awesome support, and each person having understanding your customers' needs is critical to your success.  \n\nPricing models for most help desks made it prohibitive to put this into practice because they require a seat license for every user of the platform, including casual participants. After a lot of consideration, we came up with what we believe is a unique, genuine solution. Traditional seat licensing still makes sense for \"full-time\" support agents, but in order to bring the voice of the customer to the entire organization, we have created a supplemental option called \"Flex\" hours. The spirit of Flex hours is to allow users who are not \"full-time\" agents to participate in the support experience.\r\n How Flex Hours Work \r\n    •    For your full-time support staff, buy traditional per-month seats\n•    You can then create as many Flex agent accounts as you like (create seats for your executives, developers, etc. for FREE)\n•    When Flex agents log into Desk.com, we tra