 the Agent UI - this will start generating screenpops for new and open cases (including chats) that the agent has access to. \r\n\r\n   \r\n\r\n   \r\n\r\n In addition, you can offer an email form if the offerEmailIfChatUnavailable feature is set to true. This will offer an Email button instead of a Chat button is chat is not available.   \r\n\r\n   \r\n\r\n Related Articles \r\n\r\n Adding Fields to a Widget in Desk.com \r\n\r\n Customizing the Live Chat button \r\n\r\n Redirecting waiting Chat to the E-mail Form \r\n\r\n How do I use SnapEngage with Desk.com","body_email_auto":true,"body_chat":"Desk.com offers convenient built-in links for your customers to create a conversation from anywhere in your Support Center, including Questions &amp; Answers, email and chat. Also, with the Desk.com Chat widget, you can add a chat button anywhere on ... http://j.mp/dYXiN8","body_chat_auto":true,"body_web_callback":"<p><span class=\"c3 c15\">Desk.com offers convenient built-in links for your customers to create a conversation from anywhere in your Support Center, including Questions &amp; Answers, email and chat. Also, with the Desk.com Chat widget, you can add a chat button anywhere on your own existing website, or embed the ability to chat within your Customer Support Center.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><span class=\"c3\">Steps for Adding the Chat Widget</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c1\">To add a chat button to your website that will launch the chat dialog, follow these steps. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol class=\"c12\" start=\"1\">\r\n\t<li class=\"c7 c2 c16\"><span class=\"c1\">Get your chat widget code. You can find it under Desk.com Admin Panel &rarr; Channels &rarr; Chat &rarr; Widgets</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"c2\"><b id=\"internal-source-marker_0.6549763071816415\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times; font-size: medium; font-weight: normal; \"><img height=\"392px;\" src=\"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/E0tMk4eyZTtE82P3PrH52QKO0gJcP