 for your portal. \n If you need help making your Support Center look and feel like you? Ask your account manager or contact us to learn about the Desk.com Professional Services Design Packages.","body_facebook_auto":true,"keywords":"","position":4,"quickcode":null,"in_support_center":true,"internal_notes":"","publish_at":"2013-05-10T00:00:00Z","created_at":"2013-04-24T01:58:05Z","updated_at":"2013-05-13T13:49:18Z","_links":{"self":{"href":"/api/v2/articles/1110362","class":"article"},"topic":{"href":"/api/v2/topics/499013","class":"topic"},"translations":{"href":"/api/v2/articles/1110362/translations","class":"article_translation"}}},{"subject":"Glossary","body":"<u><strong>Admin -&nbsp; </strong></u>The Admin is the area of the user interface you can utilize to set up your users, and manage your account.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Agent -&nbsp;</strong></u> The Agent is the User Interface area you can manage your customer support cases<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Reports&nbsp;</strong></u> The Reports is the area of the User Interface where you can manage your data in a Dashboard.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Rules</strong></u> - The conditions that can be changed to allow your customer support cases to be handled based on certain criteria<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Macros</strong></u> - A shortcut for creating responses or any text you would like to be displayed to the user based on certain criteria.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Cases</strong></u> -&nbsp; A case is a customer support problem that can be assigned, resolved, deleted. Cases are stored in the Agent User Interface and can have different rules assigned to them, based on a criteria set by the Administrator.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Channels</strong></u> -&nbsp; A channel is a view that can be used to include in your portal such as Twitter, Facebook or Chat.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Portal</strong> -&nbsp; Your Assistly Website that includes templates from Assitly that you can customize<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Templates -&nbsp;</strong> Emails, Customer Support responses that can be edited and customized with your text, colors, and graphics.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Filters</strong></u> -&nbsp; Business rules that will allow you to determine how you want customer support issues to be dealt with, sent to or administered based on your specific requirements<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<u><strong>Groups</strong></u> - Different users can be linked together for handling cases or support issues<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;","body_email":"Admin -  The Admin is the area of the user interface you can utilize to set up your users, and manage your account.\n\nAgent -  The Agent is the User Interface area you can manage your customer support cases\n\nReports  The Reports is the area of the User Interface where you can manage your data in a Dashboard.\n\nRules - The conditions that can be changed to allow your customer support cases to be handled based on certain criteria\n\nMacros - A shortcut for creating responses or any text you would like to be displayed to the user based on certain criteria.\n\nCases -  A case is a customer support problem that can be assigned, resolved, deleted. Cases are stored in the Agent User Interface and can have different rules assigned to them, based on a criteria set by the Administrator.\n\nChannels -  A channel is a view that can be used to include in your portal such as Twitter, Facebook or Chat.\n\nPortal -  Your Assistly Website that includes templates from Assitly that you can customize\n\nTemplates -  Emails, Customer Support responses that can be edited and customized with your text, colors, and graphics.\n\nFilters -  Business rules that will allow you to determine how you want customer support issues to be dealt with, sent to or administered based on your specific requirements\n\nGroups - Different users can be linked together for handling cases or support issues"